body:
@mtgap i just gave it a try without encryption, this seems to be still broken.

first, upgrade from stable5 to this branch stopped in maintenance mode. but i'm not sure if it was related to the sharing upgrade code. i will have to look into it. than i started over with a complete fresh installation. created two users, user1 created a text file, try to share it to user2 which results in following error message: "error while sharing: the permissions are not valid for this file". no further error messages in error.log, owncloud.log or the js console. any idea what could be wrong here?

i just debugged it a bit: the post request sends permission 31, but arevalidpermissions() in filesharebackend.php calculates 27 (which misses iscreatable because it is not a directory). sharing a folder works, because there i also have the iscreatable permission.
